text:
Every shadow has its light, every truth its lie. I've spent too much time in the dark alleys of Eldoria to miss the obvious blind spots in our economic layer here. For starters, we need to address the role of the local nobility more deeply. The wealth distribution seems a bit off—40% for landowners is too high, especially considering their often absentee presence compared to the daily struggles of farmers and craftsmen.

Let's refine this. In Eldoria Village, the actual landowners are few but powerful. They control not just property rights, but also major trade routes through bribes and subtle manipulation. The farmers and craftsmen are exploited by these landed gentry who sit idle in their manors, collecting rents while the common folk toil under harsh conditions. We should revise our wealth distribution to reflect this reality:

```json
